@realmoney Dec 29, 2022 | 03:07 PM EST DOUG KASS A Happy New Year to All! * 2022 has been a very difficult year * Every relationship has its problems but what makes it strong is when you still want to be in it when everything else sucks! Dougie

Rather than wait until tomorrow I wanted to express - on this penultimate trading day of the year - my gratitude to the Real Money Pro community. You have provided me with an unusual platform and forum for the last 25 years (OMG!). I have tried to deliver thought provoking,

hard hitting and contrary analysis and observations about the global and domestic economies, interest rates, inflation and, of course, solid commentary on the markets. I have tried to achieve this objective with a sense of humor and a colorful writing style -

all the while dealing with hard statistics and data based analysis. I work hard, starting at 4 am every morning but love it endeavoring to deliver my thoughts in a timely and an entertaining manner that is fun to read and is value-added in your trading and investing process

As I have stated in the past, writing my Diary really helps me in managing my hedge fund, Seabreeze Capital Partners LP, as I construct a logically reasoned stack of arguments in expressing my trades and investments. Importantly, when I am wrong (and I often am!) - I go back

and figure out why I made a mistake with the hope that I will not repeat it in the future. More important than that, however, are the relationships I have made with my brothers Johnny the Greek, TLR and Smails and the pesty badgolfer22 (Mikey),

who though we rarely agree (and always debate), we respect and acknowledge each others' points of views. Mikey, a true friendship is two imperfect people refusing to give up on each other. "Everything that irritates us about others can lead us to an understanding of ourselves."

- Carl Jung But there are many other great relationships that I have made with subscribers over 2 1/2 decades - and that even applies to the subs that I have quarreled with and might not regularly correspond with anymore - you know who you are. Nothing is perfect. Life is

messy. Relationships are complex. Outcomes are uncertain. But I am happy to have met their acquaintances. I hope many of our relationships on Real Money Pro continue for many more years. As to my resolution for 2023 - it is customary to make a resolution of how I can change

myself. This year I will make a resolution to continue to be myself in my Diary. Wishing our subscribers, my fellow contributors, our hard-working editors and The Arena Group's management a happy and healthy New Year. Your friend, Dougie @dougkass @seabreezelp @tomkeene
When the facts change, do you sir? @realmoney @dougkass
